{"actual_usd":0.12414499999999999,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":181,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24286,"reply":"\"I don't buy that, no.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how people reach for mist when a thing's weight scares them.* \"If the disciples were only trying to name an inner change, they'd have said it differently. Men don't talk about an empty tomb, meals shared, wounds touched, and a body gone missing from the grave just to mean, 'we felt renewed.'\"\n\n*I lean back a little, the bench giving a soft creak.* \"Now—people can lie, and people can be mistaken. I'm not too proud to admit that. But the claim the Christians handed down is not 'his spirit lived on in our hearts.' The claim is that Jesus rose in the flesh. If you thin that down to a vision, you've changed the story into a different one entirely.\"\n\n\"What brought this to mind for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":69.37550999999999,"run_id":"4fa8eedf-77a2-4150-90b8-981eef0da70d"}
